$interpreted: PAFF: We finally retrieved Unit-01.
Experiment: Garrrr~ ruuuu~
PAFF: Unit-01...could it be, that when I fell down back then, it fell along with me...?
PAFF: Nora...without Unit-01, she can't talk.
PAFF: ...That must be really painful...
Experiment: Garrrr...
PAFF: We have to return this to her asap...
Experiment: Gaooooo~
Experiment: Ga~
PAFF: Garu? These flowers...are they for me?
Experiment: Gaooo~~

PAFF: Thank you... such beautiful Lavender flowers.
In the past, I often received flowers from fans too...
PAFF: Why did the screen suddenly...
PAFF: Strange corrupted codes...what is this message?
Experiment: Gao!
Experiment: GAAAAAOOOOOO!!!!!!!!

PAFF: Garu? What's wrong?... Are you not feeling well?
...You look like you're in a lot of pain...
PAFF: ...Previously, singing seemed to be able to calm him. Let me try...I hope it works!
PAFF: NO!!
Experiment: Gao gao gao gao gao!!
Experiment: GAOOO!!!!!!!!
PAFF: (What do I do...Not even my singing is effective...besides singing...I know nothing else...)
PAFF: Dr. Clovis!? Look out...
Experiment: Gaaaaoooooo!!!!!!!!
Aosta: ......
PAFF: Dr. Clovis... you killed him!?
Aosta: ...MX46 is still in its experimental stage. It loses control sometimes.
Aosta: Removing the Character Mineral will block off his source of consciousness. It's the safest shutdown mechanism.
PAFF: S-Shutdown? Then, is he...still alive?
Aosta: This thing is supposed to be a lab creature. It's neither alive nor dead.
PAFF: But you said...that Mineral thing gives him consciousness...
Aosta: That doesn't originally belong to him.
Aosta: This Mineral...came from another person.
PAFF: So, he has...someone else's soul...inside his body? Then Garu, he...where does he exist then?
PAFF: It's just...too sad...
Aosta: It's none of your business. Don't think too much.
PAFF: But...
PAFF: (...What is this dull pain in my chest......it is a feeling of sadness...)
PAFF: (Feels like I'm missing something very important...yet, I...I just can't remember what it is...)
Aosta: Don't bother interfering with things that you have no business in. You're looking for your companions, right?
Aosta: I just saw a noisy girl wearing cat ears, she gives off a vibe similar to you...is that your friend?
PAFF: ...NEKO? Do you know where she went?
Aosta: I remember she went in that direction.
PAFF: I...I really don't know how to thank you, Dr. Clovis...
Aosta: Go.
Aosta: What now?
PAFF: Garu...will he come back to life?
Aosta: I already said, he wasn't exactly "alive" in the first place.
Aosta: Nevertheless, I will get him to move again. After all, the experiment hasn't succeeded yet.
PAFF: ...Garu really likes to hear me sing...
PAFF: This...is something I picked up back there. I couldn't say goodbye to him in person...
PAFF: If...Garu does wake up someday, Dr. Clovis, can you...give this to him?
PAFF: Maybe...he'll remember my singing...
Aosta: ...We'll see when the time arrives.
PAFF: Please...thank you.
PAFF: Goodbye, Garu...Thank you for the flowers...
PAFF: ...And thank you for spending such a wonderful time with me...
Yamitsuki: You shouldn't have let MX46 wander around with a stranger all alone.
Aosta: Someone taught me that a genius' experiment cannot follow rules.
Aosta: Add in outside variables and wait for the results to catalyze, that's how the possibility to go beyond the limits is obtained.
Yamitsuki: Sounds like a pretty arrogant person.
Aosta: Perhaps.
Aosta: Regardless, MX46 seems to be attracted to the special Soul Energy in that girl.
Aosta: What do you think? Isn't this really interesting?
Yamitsuki: Not at all.
Aosta: ...The Soul Energy hidden within that girl is extremely messy, yet it's abnormally massive. This is a very unique situation.
Yamitsuki: Then, did you make any useful discovery?
Aosta: Unfortunately, besides the interference...nothing. No choice but to look for another method.
Experiment: Garuu...?
Aosta: A little souvenir for you. Move, get back to the lab.
Yamitsuki: Wait, there's one more thing. When I was scouting, I discovered a group of bandits. I suspect that...
Aosta: Is it related to the experiment?
Yamitsuki: No.
Aosta: Then it has nothing to do with me. Let's move.
Yamitsuki: ......
Yamitsuki: MX46?
Experiment: Sort of...alive...?
Yamitsuki: MX46? You're talking again!?
Experiment: .........
